2020 Election Analysis using Twitter

Demonstrate how to access Twitter data using rtweet package.
Follow instructions for each section and include text annotation/ interpretation of results!
What can be concluded based on the data investigation?

Libraries

Common libraries

# twitter library 
library(rtweet)

# plotting and pipes - tidyverse
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr, warn.conflicts = FALSE)
options(dplyr.summarise.inform = FALSE) # Suppress summarise info

# text mining library
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(tidyverse)) # suppress startup message

# date/time libaray
library(lubridate, warn.conflicts = FALSE)

Authenticate

Use create_token initially, but once the token is created, only need to use get_token() in subsequent sessions to load the token.

# getting the token needs to be only done once. Once done, set tokenOk to TRUE
if (tokenOk==FALSE) {
  ## authenticate via web browser
  token <- create_token(
    app = "gguSentiment",
    consumer_key = api_key,
    consumer_secret = api_secret_key,
    access_token = access_token,
    access_secret = access_token_secret)
}

## check to see if the token is loaded
get_token()

Retrieve most recent 3200 timelines of Trump and Biden

  • use: JoeBiden and realDonaldTrump
  • dont exclude anything
  • save to csv file, so you dont have to call the api subsequently, in case of long delays
  • read the csv file into a dataframe and use that df for subsequent analysis.
    • You will notice using the View (df) function that the the object structure of the original dataframe after the AP call is different from the one you read in. The original has embedded list objects, whereas the one read in is flattend. Also the date/time fields such as create_at is char rather than Twitters POSIX time format. Use lubridate datetime functions (eg: as_datetime) to convert.

    • original = is_retweet==FALSE & is_quote==FALSE & is.na(reply_to_status_id)
  • summarize retweet_count, replies_count and orig_count (eg: sum of original)
  • show the summary of this transformed data frame
